article.headline: North Dakota 87, Crown (Minn.) 51
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Aaron Anderson scored 18 points Wednesday night and North Dakota breezed to an 87-51 win over Crown College of Minnesota. Lenny Antwi had a career-high 16 points for North Dakota(1-1). Anderson had eight assists and Antwi finished with seven. Antwi also grabbed seven rebounds. Josh Schuler scored 13 points and Jordan Allard added 12 points and seven rebounds for UND, which never trailed in the game. Crown tied the game at 24 with just over 6 minutes left in the first half, but North Dakota scored the next six points and went on to lead 44-31 at halftime. Truman Shetler led the Storm with 12 points and Anthony DiLoreto had 10 points and seven rebounds. Crown College plays in Division III.
